I never wanted any official claim to Native heritage it never felt right to try to draw any benefits when I’m not a member of that society if I were to live on the Reservation and be able to be active in that society it may be different otherwise it feels like stealing. I greatly appreciate everyone who commented. I’ll keep as I am having love and appreciation for all things Lakota and adapting the philosophy and culture into my life and be an Ally.

I appreciate this article! Question. If I claim to have native ancestry through family verbal history is this looked upon poorly from the perspective of the tribal members? I grew up with the story passed down that Sitting Bulls sister was a great great great Grandmother. I love all the song, history, philosophy, art, and culture I’m aware of, and that won’t change! I feel a connection in my spirit and I am trying to learn the language and teach my kids about all these things.  I’m happy to have any input.
